The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has approved Tuesday 8, March 2022 for the Lagos State Congress Appeal Panel. PDP in a statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba on Saturday said the panel is to consider appeals arising from the conduct of the State Congress in Lagos State. “The Appeal Panel is now to sit on Tuesday 8, March 2022 at the PDP National Secretariat, Wuse Zone 5, Abuja, it added. Former Governor of Katsina State, Ibrahim Shema is the Chairman of the Lagos State Congress Appeal Panel, while Sen. Jarigbe Agom Jarigbe is the Secretary. Other members of the committee are Dr Akilu Indabawa, Hajiya Inna Maryam Ciroma, Chief Emmanuel Ogidi, Hon. Aro Bamidele and Barr Oji Zawo —Member. The party enjoined all aspirants, critical stakeholders and members of PDP in Lagos State to take note.